race.description: Titan One Truck Boxes Midway Handicap (Bm64)
race.comment: Some key scratchings thin this race out considerably. PIPERITA (7) has raced exclusively in town this prep and been competitive at all four runs. Wound up late to grab fourth last start in a BM72 over 1400m at the Kensington track. Is a winner here at this trip and is perfectly placed to add to that record today. WIZARDS (4) was last at the races on Boxing Day when he flew home to be beaten in a three-way thriller over 1350m at the Beaumont circuit. Placed at two of three runs over this distance so while fresh he is a genuine contender. HYDROMETER (3) can improve dropping back to the provincials. Best recent effort was two back when he led but was claimed late and finished a length away in a BM64 over 1200m at Gosford. The last 100m here will be the test. MAILI (6) is back after a five-month spell. Usually needs a couple of runs to hit her straps but in a race lacking depth she is a top four hope. YES SIREE (10) heads the others coming off a brief spell.
